ommittee and the rules committee. his record includes the sponsorship of the national missile defense act of 1999, legislation supporting education programs and action to aid the gulf coast after hurricane katrina. before his election to the u.s. senate, senator cochran served in the u.s. house of representatives. he and his wife, the former rose clayton of new albany, mississippi, have two children and three grandchildren.</p></span>



